# Web Next.js Structure Rules

## Intent
Standardize `packages/web` for a secure, maintainable chat-first Next.js app.

## Structure Rules
- Use Next.js App Router as default (`src/app`) unless a migration exception is documented.
- Keep web-only UI in `packages/web/src/components`.
- Keep web-only helpers in `packages/web/src/lib`.
- Server actions/routes handling sensitive operations must enforce authz and policy checks.

## Integration Rules
- Clerk session/auth checks must run server-side for protected operations.
- Stream client usage in web must go through shared wrappers/contracts.
- Sentry must use redaction/scrubbing defaults that prevent PII/PHI leakage.

## Performance and Safety
- Avoid exposing sensitive payloads via client bundles, cache keys, or query params.
- Define explicit caching strategy for chat endpoints with privacy-safe boundaries.

## Prohibited
- Direct secret usage in client components.
- Bypassing shared contracts for chat or compliance-relevant payloads.